cs.SI, cs.DL, cs.IR, cs.SD, cs.DB

The paper focuses on analyzing the citation networks of publications in computer science, which suggests that it could belong to several sub-categories. The most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper specifically studies the structural features of information paths through citation networks. The second likely sub-category is cs.DL (Digital Libraries) as the paper discusses the impact of citation choices on the subsequent impact of an article. The third likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the paper analyzes the flow of information through citation networks. The fourth likely sub-category is cs.SD (Software Engineering) as the paper studies differences in information flow for specific subsets of citation networks. The fifth likely sub-category is cs.DB (Databases) as the paper deals with the analysis of large datasets of citation networks.
